  "instructions": [
    "Grind the ginger and garlic in a mortar-pestle until you get a smooth paste.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the sliced red onion and red bell pepper, and cook until they are softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in the peanut butter and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until it starts to melt.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in the heavy cream and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, or until the sauce thickens slightly.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley."
  ],
